title: Eva Kolenová
text: Eva Kolenová (born 1 May 1985) is a <a href="Slovakia">Slovak</a> <a href="women%27s%20soccer">football</a> defender currently playing for <a href="SKV%20Altenmarkt">SKV Altenmarkt</a> in <a href="Austria">Austria</a>'s <a href="%C3%96FB-Frauenliga">ÖFB-Frauenliga</a>. She has played the <a href="UEFA%20Women%27s%20Cup">UEFA Women's Cup</a> with <a href="M%C5%A0K%20%C5%BDiar%20nad%20Hronom">MŠK Žiar nad Hronom</a> and <a href="FK%20Slovan%20Duslo%20%C5%A0a%C4%BEa">Slovan Duslo Šaľa</a>, and she has been a member of the <a href="Slovakia%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Slovakia women's national team</a>. In 2010 and 2011 she was named the best Slovak player of the year.
